MERN Stack

MongoDB: A doc-based open source db.
Express: A web app framework for Node
React: A JS frontend library for building user interfaces
Node: JS environment that executes JS code outside the browser (server)

Mongoose: Schema-based solution to model app data

MongoDB Documents
Mongo stores data in binary json(BJSON)
can have nested documents(data)

MongoDB route methods
.find() - GET
.save() - POST
.findById() - GET by findById
.findByIdAndDelete() - findByIdAndDelete
.findById() -> .save() - POST instead of PUT to update. 
        or
.findByIdAndUpdate(req.params.id, req.body, {new:true}) - PUT request